Full command sequence to install Proxmox on Debian 12
1️⃣ Update Debian
apt update
apt upgrade -y
2️⃣ Install required utilities

These were needed because your system was missing them (like gpg earlier).

apt install -y curl wget gnupg2 lsb-release ca-certificates
3️⃣ Add Proxmox repository

Create the repo file:

echo "deb http://download.proxmox.com/debian/pve bookworm pve-no-subscription" \
| tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/pve-install-repo.list
4️⃣ Add Proxmox GPG key
wget https://enterprise.proxmox.com/debian/proxmox-release-bookworm.gpg \
-O /usr/share/keyrings/proxmox-release-bookworm.gpg

or

curl -fsSL https://enterprise.proxmox.com/debian/proxmox-release-bookworm.gpg \
| gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/proxmox-release-bookworm.gpg
5️⃣ Update repositories
apt update
6️⃣ Install Proxmox VE
apt install -y proxmox-ve postfix open-iscsi

During install:

Choose:

Local only

for postfix.

7️⃣ Reboot
reboot
8️⃣ Fix hostname / hosts (the issue you had)

Edit:

nano /etc/hosts

Example:

127.0.0.1 localhost
10.0.2.15 proxmox

::1 localhost ip6-localhost ip6-loopback
9️⃣ Regenerate certificates
pvecm updatecerts --force
🔟 Restart services
systemctl restart pveproxy
systemctl restart pvedaemon
systemctl restart pvestatd
1️⃣1️⃣ Check Proxmox running
ss -tulpn | grep 8006

You should see:

pveproxy listening on 8006
1️⃣2️⃣ Access panel
https://SERVER-IP:8006

or via Tailscale

https://TAILSCALE-IP:8006
Extra things you installed earlier

You also installed:

cloudflared

Tailscale

Those are just remote access tunnels, not part of Proxmox itself.

Important VPS warning

Since you're running this on a VPS, check virtualization support:

egrep -c '(vmx|svm)' /proc/cpuinfo

Result meanings:

0 = NO KVM support (VMs won't work)
1+ = KVM supported
